* Goals
- Create an nginx config to serve static pages
- Force =HTTPS=
- Canonicalize
  - Reroute everything to include the =www= subdomain
- Setup =certbot=

* =nginx= config

#+BEGIN_SRC
# Force https
server {
	listen 80;
	listen [::]:80;
	server_name example.com    www.example.com;
	return 301 https://www.example.com$request_uri;
}

# Canonicalize
server{
        listen 443 ssl;
        listen [::]:443 ssl;
        server_name example.com;

        ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/www.example.com/fullchain.pem;
        ssl_certificate_key     /etc/letsencrypt/live/www.example.com/privkey.pem;

        return 301 https://www.example.com$request_uri;

}

# Actual server
server {
        listen 443 ssl;
        listen [::]:443 ssl;
        server_name www.example.com;
  
        ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/www.example.com/fullchain.pem;
        ssl_certificate_key     /etc/letsencrypt/live/www.example.com/privkey.pem;

        location / {
                root /var/www/example.com;
        }
}
#+END_SRC
  
 - Setup a catch-all to force HTTPS
 - Canonicalize non-www requests to www
 - Serve the requests
   
* SSL certificates
- Make sure that the SSL certificate contains both the domains
  - i.e =www.example.com= and =example.com=
- This is because SSL connections happen first. So even though we will never use the non-www version
  if we have to get a SSL certificate for it. If we don't have a certificate then the client can never
  make a connection

* Certbot
- Make sure that you listen on both IPv4 and IPv6.
- Don't know if it is official but certbot sometimes requests using IPv6 and if you don't listen on that
  the challenge fails
- Use the =--webroot= option with nginx. This allows automatic renewals without stopping nginx and allows flexibility
  in the nginx config. Using the ==--nginx== also works but the automatic editing by certbot caused issues in the past
  for me.
- Check using =certbot renew --verbose --dry-run=
- Newer versions of certbot include a systemd unit to manage renewals. So the old way of cronjob is not necessary anymore.
  
  
